tcpdump
Command-line packet analyzer

Sniffing & Spoofing
Description
tcpdump is a powerful command-line packet analyzer. It allows you to capture and display TCP/IP packets transmitted over a network.

Installation / Check
Check if installed:

which tcpdump
Install command:

sudo apt install tcpdump
Basic Syntax
tcpdump [options] [expression]
Common Commands
Command	What it does	When to use	Risk
sudo tcpdump -i eth0

Capture on interface	Basic capture	
sudo tcpdump -i eth0 -w capture.pcap

Save to file	Record traffic	
sudo tcpdump -i eth0 port 80

HTTP traffic only	Filter by port	
sudo tcpdump -i eth0 host 192.168.1.100

Specific host	Monitor host	
sudo tcpdump -i eth0 -A

ASCII output	Read packet data	
sudo tcpdump -r capture.pcap

Read capture file	Analyze saved capture	
